title: British Pathé
description: Before television people came to movie theatres to watch the news. British Pathé was at the forefront of cinematic journalism blending information with entertainment to popular effect. Over the course of a century it documented everything from major armed conflicts and seismic political crises to the curious hobbies and eccentric lives of ordinary people. If it happened British Pathé filmed it.  Now considered to be the finest newsreel archive in the world British Pathé is a treasure trove of 85000 films unrivalled in their historical and cultural significance.  ALL RIGHTS RESERVED

title: Highway 11 Films
description: Highway 11 Films produces Feature films Short Films Music Videos and experimental pieces. Most of our work revolves around music and we've specialized in live music performances and live audio recording since 2003.   Our feature documentary/concert movie "Tall Corn Euforia" was officially selected to the Julien Dubuque International Film Festival and  screened April 4-7 2013 in Dubuque IA.  Our short film "Valley of Vengeance" won best sound design in the 2011 Madison 48 hour film festival.  Our short film "The Industry of Nature" won a best animation and special effects award at the Griffin film festival 2009.  Andy Steil and Dean Wellman were both editors on "Striking Out" which won a best acting award in the 2009 Madison 48 hr film festival.  Andy Steil and Dean Wellman were both involved as editors and sound design tech's in "Special Delivery" which won best use of genre in the 2010 Madison 48hr film festival.
